 and interpretation for OIIX A1010/26, the core source for the alleged Iran-initiated closure effective May 22-25, 2026.\",\"retrieval_timestamp\":\"2026-06-19T21:39:00Z\",\"sha256\":\"c909c4e719606de87221b5ae5da7b8a15936e3dba215f3859d3eafb87cd3e16f\",\"size_bytes\":1690,\"source_description\":\"Notamify page for Tehran FIR/OIIX NOTAM A1010/26, captured via web.open during plaintiff merits investigation.\",\"source_url\":\"https://notamify.com/notams/OIIX/693f2d0f-54d3-433b-8128-49f5475ba269\",\"storage_name\":\"c9/c909c4e719606de87221b5ae5da7b8a15936e3dba215f3859d3eafb87cd3e16f\",\"submitted_by_role\":\"plaintiff\",\"submitted_phase\":\"arguments\",\"text_readable\":true,\"title\":\"Notamify OIIX A1010/26 raw NOTAM capture\"},{\"admissibility_status\":\"submitted_evidence\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-19T21:43:03Z\",\"evidence_id\":\"ev_d104b8c2ce1a_submitted-evidence-05-defendant-d104b8c2ce1a\",\"mime_type\":\"text/plain\",\"original_name\":\"submitted-evidence-05-defendant-d104b8c2ce1a.txt\",\"record_visibility\":\"juror_visible\",\"relevance\":\"Explains the NOTAM Q-code structure and decodes the raw NOTAM codes at issue: FA means aerodrome, AF means flight information region, and LC means closed. Supports distinguishing A1010/26 (QFALC, aerodrome closed) from an FIR airspace closure code (QAFLC).\",\"retrieval_timestamp\":\"2026-06-19T21:44:20Z\",\"sha256\":\"d104b8c2ce1a72411c7d78476f09d933e1533cdeb283fc2e15fd890512738ea7\",\"size_bytes\":1208,\"source_description\":\"FAA Order 7930.2 Appendix B, International NOTAM (Q) Codes, captured by web.open/find during defendant merits investigation.\",\"source_url\":\"https://www.faa.gov/air_traffic/publications/atpubs/notam_html/appendix_b.html\",\"storage_name\":\"d1/d104b8c2ce1a72411c7d78476f09d933e1533cdeb283fc2e15fd890512738ea7\",\"submitted_by_role\":\"defendant\",\"submitted_phase\":\"arguments\",\"text_readable\":true,\"title\":\"FAA international NOTAM Q-code decode: FA/AF and LC\"},{\"admissibility_status\":\"ca