h limited exceptions\n\nThe market rule defines a \"major closure\" as a broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from Iranian airspace or a major Iranian airspace region. While the NOTAM uses QFALC coding (for aerodrome rather than airspace), the actual operational impact closes significant portions of the western Tehran FIR with very limited exceptions. Although the Q-code analysis makes the case closer than it might appear at first glance, on balance of the evidence I agree with the majority of my fellow council members who determined this constitutes a major closure under the market definition - it has a very broad impact on operations in a major Iranian airspace region with only limited exceptions allowed by the Iranian Civil Aviation Authority.\n\nI will submit my vote:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7d4a08d68e0142e1bd5946e5","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted record shows Iran's CAA issued NOTAM A1010/26 which closed all airports in the western part of Tehran FIR with only 8 remaining operational under strict daylight-only limitations requiring new CAA permission for civil IFR passenger flights. Despite the QFALC aerodrome coding, this constituted a broad suspension of commercial flights arriving in and departing from a major Iranian airspace region with only limited exceptions allowed by Iran, satisfying the market's definition of a major closure including under the market's limited-exceptions provision.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-coder-plus","usage":{"input":3061,"output":567,"cacheRead":45568,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49196,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781907011597,"responseId":"gen-1781907011-p7AqNkbHJc66bO6ZFDo6"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","t